fering sustained analyses of the wide range of works, with particular attention to newly discovered films and lesser-known filmmakers. Based on extensive archival work and preservation, this collection includes a complete filmography of the movement, over 100 illustrations (most of which are previously unpublished), and a bibliography of primary and secondary materials. This is an indispensible sourcebook for scholars and enthusiasts, establishing the key role played by the L.A. Rebellion within the histories of cinema, Black visual culture, and postwar art in Los Angeles.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aAfrican American motion picture producers and directorsxHistoryx20th centuryxCaliforniaxLos AngelesxCaliforniaxLos Angeles. 0aAfrican American motion picture producers and directorszCaliforniazLos AngelesxHistoryy20th century. 0aExperimental filmsxHistoryx20th centuryxCaliforniaxLos Angeles. 0aExperimental filmszCaliforniazLos AngelesxHistoryy20th century. 0aIndependent filmmakersxHistoryx20th centuryxCaliforniaxLos Angeles. 0aIndependent filmmakerszCaliforniazLos AngelesxHistoryy20th century. 0aIndependent filmsxHistoryx20th centuryxCaliforniaxLos Angeles. 0aIndependent filmszCaliforniazLos AngelesxHistoryy20th century. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh1 aField, Allyson, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package 2000-2015z978311066334108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311062111208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUCal Press eBook Package 2014-2016z978311065748740uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520960435423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520960435.jpg  a978-3-11-0